{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"06560f1feab0827f0d686b6d2db4113b","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nWhen the factsheet is stale in `cluster_consult` (`src/clusterConsult.ts:62-79`):\n\n1. **`findStaleFiles()`** (line 198-214) compares stored file hashes against current on-disk files — any file that changed, was deleted, or can't be read is flagged stale.\n\n2. **If stale files exist** (line 63):\n   - `db.markClusterFactsheetStale()` — marks the factsheet stale in the DB\n   - `db.logClusterEvent({ eventType: \"cluster_refresh_required\" })` — logs with changed file details\n   - Returns **`ErrorPayload`** with `ERROR_CODES.CLUSTER_FACTSHEET_STALE` — the MCP call fails immediately\n\n3. **The caller** (fallback trigger in `src/tools.ts`) catches this error and re-issues the question via regular `claude_consult`, preserving the answer.\n\nThe error message is `\"Cluster factsheet is stale. Run cluster_refresh before consulting.\"` (`src/errors.ts:43`)."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":30300,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a98a6ed-25c1-48bd-9e45-4b46fc252c99","uuid":"07f1b04f-02d5-4448-aa86-e2fff81a9e42"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":11148,"duration_api_ms":11113,"num_turns":1,"result":"\n\nWhen the factsheet is stale in `cluster_consult` (`src/clusterConsult.ts:62-79`):\n\n1. **`findStaleFiles()`** (line 198-214) compares stored file hashes against current on-disk files — any file that changed, was deleted, or can't be read is flagged stale.\n\n2. **If stale files exist** (line 63):\n   - `db.markClusterFactsheetStale()` — marks the factsheet stale in the DB\n   - `db.logClusterEvent({ eventType: \"cluster_refresh_required\" })` — logs with changed file details\n   - Returns **`ErrorPayload`** with `ERROR_CODES.CLUSTER_FACTSHEET_STALE` — the MCP call fails immediately\n\n3. **The caller** (fallback trigger in `src/tools.ts`) catches this error and re-issues the question via regular `claude_consult`, preserving the answer.\n\nThe error message is `\"Cluster factsheet is stale. Run cluster_refresh before consulting.\"` (`src/errors.ts:43`).","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"0a98a6ed-25c1-48bd-9e45-4b46fc252c99","total_cost_usd":0.046511000000000004,"usage":{"input_tokens":2781,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":52512,"output_tokens":254,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"MiniMax-M2.7":{"inputTokens":2781,"outputTokens":254,"cacheReadInputTokens":52512,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.046511000000000004,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"a609f3ed-e86e-4a3a-a07f-b9b23ad0341f"}
